# Ansible Vault Password Example
# 
# To use Ansible Vault for secrets:
# 
# 1. Create a vault password file:
#    echo "your-secure-vault-password" > .vault_pass
#    chmod 600 .vault_pass
# 
# 2. Add .vault_pass to .gitignore (already done)
# 
# 3. Encrypt sensitive variables:
#    ansible-vault encrypt_string 'db_password_here' --name 'db_password'
# 
# 4. Create encrypted vars files:
#    ansible-vault create group_vars/all/vault.yml
# 
# 5. Run playbooks with vault:
#    ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/main.yml --vault-password-file .vault_pass
# 
# 6. Edit encrypted files:
#    ansible-vault edit group_vars/all/vault.yml --vault-password-file .vault_pass
# 
# Best Practices:
# - Use different vault passwords per environment
# - Rotate vault passwords regularly
# - Store vault passwords in a secure password manager
# - Never commit .vault_pass to version control
# - Use ansible-vault for all sensitive data (passwords, keys, tokens)
